## Activity

-   Take the multinomial for example


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
samples_activity<-rmultinom(1e4, size = 3, prob = c(2,4,7))

#I can sum each row and visulize the summation value in one figure.

act_sum<-rowSums(samples_activity)
samples_activity_1<-data.frame(x = c(1:3),
                               y = act_sum)

ggplot(samples_activity_1, aes(x=x, y=y))+
  geom_col()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Lab_2_Activity_files/figure-pdf/unnamed-chunk-8-1.pdf){fig-pos='H'}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
#Or I can visualize each event using three figures.

#ggplot does not handle rows well, please put the data you want to visualize on columns using command `t`.

samples_activity_2<-as.data.frame(t(samples_activity))

ggplot(samples_activity_2, aes(x = samples_activity_2[,1]))+
  geom_bar()
```

